                        "text_Hi9N7i": {
                          "type": "text",
                          "settings": {
                            "text": "<p><strong>🌳 DHM</strong> (from Japanese Raisin Tree) directly boosts ALDH2 activity and accelerates acetaldehyde break down.</p><p><strong>🥑 S-Acetyl Glutathione</strong> is a highly bioavailable form of glutathione, which <a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22615054/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22615054/\">binds directly to acetaldehyde</a> to facilitate its removal and supports its <a href=\"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11479010/#:~:text=However%2C%20there%20was%20no%20significant,the%20relief%20of%20hangover%20symptoms.\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11479010/#:~:text=However%2C%20there%20was%20no%20significant,the%20relief%20of%20hangover%20symptoms.\">enzymatic breakdown</a>.</p><p><strong>🥦 Succinic Acid </strong>supports mitochondrial energy production in liver cells, keeping them metabolically active so the detox process doesn't slow down when it matters most.</p>",
