                      "settings": {
                        "text": "<p>Alcohol relaxes you by amplifying GABA (calming) and suppressing glutamate (invigorating). Your brain compensates by dialling back GABA sensitivity, and increasing glutamate activity.</p><p>When the alcohol clears, those adjustments are still in place and your brain overshoots into an overstimulated state, showing up as brain fog and fatigue. That's why drinking more alcohol the next morning might ironically help you feel better (but just delays the crash).</p>",
