                  "blocks": {
                    "text_Y7JCWd": {
                      "type": "text",
                      "name": "t:names.text",
                      "settings": {
                        "text": "<p>This is simpler than the supplement industry wants you to believe. </p><p>Alcohol suppresses the hormone that signals your kidneys to retain water, so you lose more fluid than you take in - and electrolytes go with it. </p><p>Dehydration contributes meaningfully to headaches and fatigue. The fix is straightforward: <strong>drink water.</strong> A glass between drinks, and a large glass before bed.</p>",
